## When Adding New Features

1. **Follow Existing Patterns**: Match the structure of similar modules
2. **Add Permissions**: Define in [backend/constants/permissions.js](mdc:backend/constants/permissions.js)
3. **Create Model**: Define schema in `backend/models/`
4. **Create Controller**: Business logic in `backend/controllers/`
5. **Create Routes**: API routes in `backend/routes/`
6. **Add to Server**: Register routes in [backend/server.js](mdc:backend/server.js)
7. **Create Frontend API**: Add functions to [frontend/src/utils/api.ts](mdc:frontend/src/utils/api.ts)
8. **Create Pages**: Add page components in `frontend/src/pages/`
9. **Add Routes**: Register in [frontend/src/App.tsx](mdc:frontend/src/App.tsx)
10. **Add Navigation**: Add menu items to [frontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx](mdc:frontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx)
11. **Update Permissions**: Add to [frontend/src/utils/permissions.ts](mdc:frontend/src/utils/permissions.ts)
12. **Seed Roles**: Run seed script to update admin role

## UX Guidelines for Healthcare

1. **Speed is Critical**: Minimize clicks, optimize workflows
2. **Error Prevention**: Validation, confirmation dialogs for critical actions
3. **Accessibility**: Keyboard navigation, screen reader support
4. **Mobile Responsive**: All features work on mobile devices
5. **Data Privacy**: Clear indication of sensitive data, proper access controls
6. **Audit Trail**: Track who did what and when
7. **Offline Capability**: Consider offline mode for critical functions
